Package: neatStats
Title: An R Package for Neat and Painless Statistical Reporting
Version: 0.2.1
Date: 2019-07-10
Authors@R: person("Gáspár", "Lukács", email = "lkcsgaspar@gmail.com", 
  role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-9401-4830"))
Description: This package focuses on user-friendly, clear and simple
  statistics, primarily for publication in psychological science. The main
  functions are wrappers for other packages, but there are various additions 
  as well. Every relevant step from data aggregation to reportable printed
  statistics is covered for basic experimental designs.
URL: https://github.com/gasparl/neatstats
Depends: R (>= 3.4.0)
Imports: bayestestR, pROC, MBESS, ez, BayesFactor, Exact, ggplot2, grDevices, stats
Suggests: rstudioapi
License: BSD_2_clause + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
